ai-patthana16.26:0.2_0: Having given the immaculateness of the Dhamma
ai-patthana16.26:1.1_0: For pleasant feeling the teaching associated with pleasant feeling, it doesn’t give rise to pleasant feeling, and if it doesn’t give rise to the cause or reason.
ai-patthana16.26:1.1_1: For pleasant feeling the teaching associated with pleasant feeling, and no conditions don’t give rise to painful feeling.
ai-patthana16.26:1.1_2: The thing associated with pleasant feeling ...
ai-patthana16.26:2.1_0: For painful feeling the teaching associated with painful feeling ...
ai-patthana16.26:3.1_0: As a neutral feeling arises dependent on a neutral feeling, it doesn’t give rise to pleasant feeling. ...
ai-patthana16.26:3.1_2: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana16.26:4.1_0: ‘... for the sake of all fourteenth ... the result ... the result of non-existence ... the all-factored ... the various.’
ai-patthana16.26:5.1_2: Pleasant feeling don’t give rise to pleasant feeling, and painful feeling conditioned by painful feeling.
ai-patthana16.26:7.1_0: Neutral feeling arises dependent on a neutral feeling. It doesn’t give rise to the pleasant feeling.
ai-patthana16.26:7.1_1: This is the section in brief.
